---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';

const breadcrumbItems = [
    { label: 'About' }
];
---

<Layout title="About Us - PBL Future Labs">
    <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbItems} />

        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section class="py-12 mb-12">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About us</h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">We help K-12 educators use AI to do project-based learning better. Everything we teach comes from working directly with students and schools.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Origin Story -->
        <section class="mb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border border-amber-100 rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-10">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Where this came from</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                <p>
                    When ChatGPT arrived, the PBL community didn't have a clear answer for how to use it. Teachers either ignored it or added a chatbot to their worksheets.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Phil Alcock (Australian educator, now in Acapulco) and Thom Markham (author of three books on PBL, 15+ years working with schools) started asking: What if AI actually made project-based learning better? Not a replacement, but a tool that removes the design work that takes weeks.
                </p>
                <p>
                    They spent two years prototyping with real schools. What they built is PBL 2.0—a framework for using AI at every stage of a project, from design to assessment. Faster, more differentiated, more human than before.
                </p>
                <p>
                    PBL Future Labs is where they share that work. Courses. Books. Direct coaching with schools. Everything tested with real students first.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Team -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">The Team</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <!-- Phil -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
                    <div class="text-center mb-4">
                        <div class="w-24 h-24 bg-amber-100 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center text-4xl">P</div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Phil Alcock</h3>
                        <p class="text-amber-700 font-medium">Founder</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-3">
                        <p>
                            Australian educator now based in Acapulco. Phil is a systems thinker who brings a neurodivergent lens (ADHD/autism) to learning design. This means his frameworks work for all learners, not just the typical ones.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            He speaks at ISTE, has guest lectured at Harvard, and has 10K+ educators following his work on AI in education. He founded PBL Future Labs to build the bridge between AI tools and classroom reality.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-xs rounded-full">ISTE Speaker</span>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-xs rounded-full">Harvard Guest Lecturer</span>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-xs rounded-full">Systems Thinker</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-4 flex gap-3">
                        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/phillipalcock" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium no-underline">LinkedIn &rarr;</a>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Thom -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
                    <div class="text-center mb-4">
                        <img src="/images/thom.webp" alt="Thom Markham" width="96" height="96" class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover mx-auto mb-4 border-4 border-white shadow-lg" />
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Thom Markham, Ph.D.</h3>
                        <p class="text-blue-700 font-medium">Author & PBL Expert</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-3">
                        <p>
                            Ph.D. in Psychology, author of three books on PBL, and has trained thousands of educators worldwide over 15+ years. Thom is the recognized expert on how project-based learning actually works.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            At PBL Future Labs, Thom ensures our AI work is grounded in real learning science. His frameworks guarantee that AI makes learning better, not just faster or cheaper.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-xs rounded-full">3 Published Books</span>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-xs rounded-full">Keynote Speaker</span>
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-xs rounded-full">Ph.D. Psychology</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-4 flex gap-3">
                        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/thommarkham" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium no-underline">LinkedIn &rarr;</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Acapulco Learning Lab -->
        <section class="mb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border border-teal-100 rounded-2xl p-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The learning lab</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                <p>
                    We're based in Acapulco, Mexico. That's deliberate. We work outside the US education bubble, which means we test ideas across cultures and contexts, not just one school district.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The lab is where we prototype new workflows, develop courses, and run pilots with schools worldwide. It also proves that meaningful education work can happen anywhere—you don't need a Silicon Valley address to do work that matters.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- What We Actually Do -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What We Offer</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Courses</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">4-7 week online programs with concrete AI + PBL skills. Each includes projects you implement with your own students.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Books</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Thom's three books on modern PBL practice, available with a context guide connecting them to how AI changes things.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Coaching</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Anything from single workshops to multi-year school partnerships. Virtual or in-person, built around your goals.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Curriculum Design</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Custom curriculum design services for schools implementing PBL 2.0 across departments or entire systems.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Who This Is For -->
        <section class="mb-16 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-10">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Who we work with</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">Teachers</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Using or wanting to use PBL. You need practical ways to use AI in your projects—not hype.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">Curriculum leaders</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Building AI + PBL frameworks across departments or your whole district. We scale with you.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">School leaders</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Ready to give your teachers concrete tools instead of empty AI training or fear-based restrictions.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">International educators</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Our frameworks work across cultures and contexts. They're not built for one region.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <section class="py-12 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-2xl text-center mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to start?</h2>
            <p class="text-lg mb-6 opacity-90">Browse courses, read books, or get in touch to discuss coaching for your school.</p>
            <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
                <a href="/courses" class="btn btn-lg bg-white text-blue-600 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-xl px-8 no-underline min-h-[48px] active:scale-95 transition-transform">Courses</a>
                <a href="mailto:hello@pblfuturelabs.com" class="btn btn-lg btn-ghost text-white hover:bg-white/20 rounded-xl px-8 no-underline min-h-[48px] active:scale-95 transition-transform">Contact</a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <section class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Get In Touch</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <p class="text-gray-700">Have questions or want to collaborate? We'd like to hear from you.</p>
                <div class="flex gap-2 items-center">
                    <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Email:</span>
                    <a href="mailto:hello@pblfuturelabs.com" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 no-underline">hello@pblfuturelabs.com</a>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2 items-center">
                    <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Connect:</span>
                    <div class="flex gap-3">
                        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/phillipalcock" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 no-underline">Phil on LinkedIn</a>
                        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/thommarkham" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 no-underline">Thom on LinkedIn</a>
                        <a href="https://youtube.com/@pblglobal" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 no-underline">YouTube</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-2 items-center">
                    <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Location:</span>
                    <span class="text-gray-700">Acapulco, Mexico</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</Layout>
